  "prompt": "Which is the best headphone for \"Moto G 2nd gen\"?",
  "response": "The Moto G 2nd Gen, released in 2014, features a standard 3.5mm headphone jack, so it is compatible with most wired headphones. However, since it does not support high-end audio codecs like aptX or LDAC, you don't necessarily need ultra-high-end headphones to get the best experience. Here are some great headphone options that pair well with the Moto G 2nd Gen:\n\n---\n\n### **Best Budget Options:**\n1. **Sony MDR-ZX110**  \n   - Affordable and lightweight.  \n   - Decent sound quality for the price.  \n\n2. **Panasonic ErgoFit RP-TCM125**  \n   - In-ear headphones with a comfortable fit.  \n   - Great value for everyday use.  \n\n3. **JBL T110**  \n   - Compact in-ear design with good bass.  \n   - Durable and affordable.  \n\n---\n\n### **Mid-Range Options:**\n1. **Sennheiser HD 206**  \n   - Over-ear headphones with clear sound.  \n   - Comfortable for long listening sessions.  \n\n2. **Audio-Technica ATH-M20x**  \n   - Studio-quality sound for the price.  \n   - Ideal for music enthusiasts.  \n\n3. **Skullcandy Crusher Evo**  \n   - Wireless (Bluetooth) or wired use.  \n   - Strong bass and modern design.  \n\n---\n\n### **Premium Options:**\n1. **Sony WH-CH720N**  \n   - Wireless noise-canceling headphones.  \n   - Excellent sound quality and long battery life.  \n\n2. **Bose QuietComfort 35 II**  \n   - Industry-leading noise cancellation.  \n   - Comfortable and premium build.  \n\n3. **Sennheiser Momentum 3 Wireless**  \n   - High-end sound quality.  \n   - Stylish design with great features.  \n\n---\n\n### **Tips for Choosing:**\n- If you prefer wired headphones, stick to options with a 3.5mm jack.  \n- For wireless headphones, ensure they support basic Bluetooth codecs (SBC or AAC) since the Moto G 2nd Gen doesn't support aptX or LDAC.  \n- Consider comfort and build quality based on your usage (e.g., commuting, gym, or home listening).  \n\nLet me know if you'd like more specific recommendations!",
